headlines.description: — With Kemba Walker and Evan Fournier, the New York Knicks can do things they couldn't last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker scores 19, Knicks romp to end 15-game skid vs 76ers

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Golden State coach Steve Kerr's plan to get Stephen Curry some extra rest didn't turn out quite how he'd hoped.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 23, Warriors top Thunder to remain unbeaten

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 26 points and 14 rebounds, Reggie Bullock had his best game with his new team by scoring 16 points and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Houston Rockets 116-106 in coach Jason Kidd's first home game Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs beat Rockets 116-106 in Kidd's home debut

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Davis had 35 points and 17 rebounds, Russell Westbrook added 33 points and 10 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Lakers rallied without LeBron James to beat the San Antonio Spurs 125-121 in overtime Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis, Westbrook lead Lakers by Spurs minus James, 125-121

headlines.description: — Without the injured Nikola Jokic on the court, Rudy Gobert gladly took center stage down the stretch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert leads Jazz over Nuggets 122-110 as Jokic gets hurt
